23/* define NO_GZIP when compiling if you want to disable gzip header and
24 trailer decoding by inflate(). NO_GZIP would be used to avoid linking in
25 the crc code when it is not needed. For shared libraries, gzip decoding
26 should be left enabled. */
27#ifndef NO_GZIP
28# define GUNZIP
29#endif

31/* Possible inflate modes between inflate() calls */
32typedef enum {
33 HEAD, /* i: waiting for magic header */
34 FLAGS, /* i: waiting for method and flags (gzip) */
35 TIME, /* i: waiting for modification time (gzip) */
36 OS, /* i: waiting for extra flags and operating system (gzip) */
37 EXLEN, /* i: waiting for extra length (gzip) */
38 EXTRA, /* i: waiting for extra bytes (gzip) */
39 NAME, /* i: waiting for end of file name (gzip) */
40 COMMENT, /* i: waiting for end of comment (gzip) */
41 HCRC, /* i: waiting for header crc (gzip) */
42 DICTID, /* i: waiting for dictionary check value */
43 DICT, /* waiting for inflateSetDictionary() call */
44 TYPE, /* i: waiting for type bits, including last-flag bit */
45 TYPEDO, /* i: same, but skip check to exit inflate on new block */
46 STORED, /* i: waiting for stored size (length and complement) */
47 COPY_, /* i/o: same as COPY below, but only first time in */
48 COPY, /* i/o: waiting for input or output to copy stored block */
49 TABLE, /* i: waiting for dynamic block table lengths */
50 LENLENS, /* i: waiting for code length code lengths */
51 CODELENS, /* i: waiting for length/lit and distance code lengths */
52 LEN_, /* i: same as LEN below, but only first time in */
53 LEN, /* i: waiting for length/lit/eob code */
54 LENEXT, /* i: waiting for length extra bits */
55 DIST, /* i: waiting for distance code */
56 DISTEXT, /* i: waiting for distance extra bits */
57 MATCH, /* o: waiting for output space to copy string */
58 LIT, /* o: waiting for output space to write literal */
59 CHECK, /* i: waiting for 32-bit check value */
60 LENGTH, /* i: waiting for 32-bit length (gzip) */
61 DONE, /* finished check, done -- remain here until reset */
62 BAD, /* got a data error -- remain here until reset */
63 MEM, /* got an inflate() memory error -- remain here until reset */
64 SYNC /* looking for synchronization bytes to restart inflate() */
65} inflate_mode;
66
67/*
68 State transitions between above modes -
69
70 (most modes can go to BAD or MEM on error -- not shown for clarity)
71
72 Process header:
73 HEAD -> (gzip) or (zlib) or (raw)
74 (gzip) -> FLAGS -> TIME -> OS -> EXLEN -> EXTRA -> NAME -> COMMENT ->
75 HCRC -> TYPE
76 (zlib) -> DICTID or TYPE
77 DICTID -> DICT -> TYPE
78 (raw) -> TYPEDO
79 Read deflate blocks:
80 TYPE -> TYPEDO -> STORED or TABLE or LEN_ or CHECK
81 STORED -> COPY_ -> COPY -> TYPE
82 TABLE -> LENLENS -> CODELENS -> LEN_
83 LEN_ -> LEN
84 Read deflate codes in fixed or dynamic block:
85 LEN -> LENEXT or LIT or TYPE
86 LENEXT -> DIST -> DISTEXT -> MATCH -> LEN
87 LIT -> LEN
88 Process trailer:
89 CHECK -> LENGTH -> DONE
90 */
91
92/* state maintained between inflate() calls. Approximately 10K bytes. */
93struct inflate_state {
94 inflate_mode mode; /* current inflate mode */
95 int last; /* true if processing last block */
96 int wrap; /* bit 0 true for zlib, bit 1 true for gzip */
97 int havedict; /* true if dictionary provided */
98 int flags; /* gzip header method and flags (0 if zlib) */
99 unsigned dmax; /* zlib header max distance (INFLATE_STRICT) */
100 unsigned long check; /* protected copy of check value */
101 unsigned long total; /* protected copy of output count */
102 gz_headerp head; /* where to save gzip header information */
103 /* sliding window */
104 unsigned wbits; /* log base 2 of requested window size */
105 unsigned wsize; /* window size or zero if not using window */
106 unsigned whave; /* valid bytes in the window */
107 unsigned wnext; /* window write index */
108 unsigned char FAR *window; /* allocated sliding window, if needed */
109 /* bit accumulator */
110 unsigned long hold; /* input bit accumulator */
111 unsigned bits; /* number of bits in "in" */
112 /* for string and stored block copying */
113 unsigned length; /* literal or length of data to copy */
114 unsigned offset; /* distance back to copy string from */
115 /* for table and code decoding */
116 unsigned extra; /* extra bits needed */
117 /* fixed and dynamic code tables */
118 code const FAR *lencode; /* starting table for length/literal codes */
119 code const FAR *distcode; /* starting table for distance codes */
120 unsigned lenbits; /* index bits for lencode */
121 unsigned distbits; /* index bits for distcode */
122 /* dynamic table building */
123 unsigned ncode; /* number of code length code lengths */
124 unsigned nlen; /* number of length code lengths */
125 unsigned ndist; /* number of distance code lengths */
126 unsigned have; /* number of code lengths in lens[] */
127 code FAR *next; /* next available space in codes[] */
128 unsigned short lens[320]; /* temporary storage for code lengths */
129 unsigned short work[288]; /* work area for code table building */
130 code codes[ENOUGH]; /* space for code tables */
131 int sane; /* if false, allow invalid distance too far */
132 int back; /* bits back of last unprocessed length/lit */
133 unsigned was; /* initial length of match */
134};
